{
  "texts": [
    "The simulation environment is defined within a 3D space, where the cylinders have the capability to move along all three axes (x, y, z), with a constraint on their displacement not exceeding 1mm per operational cycle, equating to 1ms.",
    "The modeling of each cycle incorporates 15 numerical values, representing the spatial coordinates of the three objects (9 numbers) and the directional movements of the two cylinders (6 numbers).This simulation allows for the iterative assessment of collision detection, where inputs leading to potential collisions are classified as invalid, as collision detection is particularly meaningful in situations where collisions have not occurred yet, as we want to prevent them from happening.",
    "Case Study: 6-DOF Robot Collision DetectionThis case study explores a 6-DOF serial manipulator, capable of intricate movements in a 3D space.",
    "DOF refers to the independent movements or axes a robot can control.",
    "Figure 4.2 showcases the robot."
  ]
}